1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 12.1-17 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the dissemination of personally identifying information; to provide a
3 penalty; and to declare an emergency.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 12.1-17 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Dissemination of personally identifying information prohibited - Penalty .
8 1. As used in this section:
9 a. "Dissemination" means electronically publishing, posting, or otherwise disclosing
10 information to a public internet site or public forum.
11 b. "Household member" means an individual who:
12 (1) Regularly resides in the household; or
13 (2) Within the six months preceding the conduct of the offense regularly resided
14 in the household.
15 c. "Immediate family member" means a parent, grandparent, spouse, child,
16 stepchild, father-in - law, mother-in - law, son-in - law, daughter-in - law, sibling ,
17 brother-in - law, sister-in - law, or grandchild .
18 d. "Personally identifying information" means information that identifies or
19 reasonably can be used to identify an individual, including:
20 (1) Social security number or other government-issued identifier;
21 (2) Date of birth;
22 (3) Home or physical address;
23 (4) Electronic mail address or telephone number;
24 (5) Financial account number or credit or debit card number;
